ðŸ”¥ What is the os Module in Python?
The os module lets Python interact with the Operating System â€” Windows, Linux, macOS.
With os, you can:
âœ… Work with files & folders
âœ… Run system commands
âœ… Read environment variables
âœ… Change directories
âœ… Get system information
â€¦ and so much more!
This module is heavily used in automation, DevOps scripts, CI/CD, and system administration.

ðŸš€ Most Important os Module Features (Explained)
1ï¸âƒ£ os.getcwd() â€“ Get Current Working Directory
import os
print(os.getcwd())


ðŸ’¡ Useful for understanding where your script is running.
2ï¸âƒ£ os.chdir() â€“ Change Directory
os.chdir("/var/log")
print(os.getcwd())


Switch your working folderâ€”great for log reading, file automation.
3ï¸âƒ£ os.listdir() â€“ List Files in a Directory
print(os.listdir("/etc"))

Perfect for monitoring directories or automation scripts.
4ï¸âƒ£ os.mkdir() / os.makedirs() â€“ Create Folders
os.mkdir("testfolder")
os.makedirs("a/b/c")  # creates nested folders

5ï¸âƒ£ os.remove() â€“ Delete Files
os.remove("old.log")

6ï¸âƒ£ os.rmdir() / os.removedirs() â€“ Remove Directories
os.rmdir("testfolder")

7ï¸âƒ£ os.rename() â€“ Rename File or Folder
os.rename("oldname.txt", "newname.txt")

8ï¸âƒ£ os.environ â€“ Environment Variables
print(os.environ["HOME"])

Used heavily in DevOps, especially loading secrets like DB passwords.
9ï¸âƒ£ os.system() â€“ Execute Shell Commands
os.system("ls -l")

âš ï¸ For more advanced usage, prefer subprocess module.
ðŸ’¥ FULL WORKING EXAMPLE
This example shows various OS operations together:

import os
# 1. Show current working directory
print("Current Directory:", os.getcwd())
# 2. Create a new folder
os.mkdir("demo_folder")
print("Folder created!")
# 3. Change into that folder
os.chdir("demo_folder")
print("Directory changed to:", os.getcwd())
# 4. Create a file inside it
with open("test.txt", "w") as f:
    f.write("Hello from Python os module!")
print("File created successfully.")
# 5. List directory contents
print("Files inside folder:", os.listdir())
# 6. Rename the file
os.rename("test.txt", "renamed.txt")
print("File renamed!")
# 7. Delete the file
os.remove("renamed.txt")
print("File removed!")
# 8. Go back and delete folder
os.chdir("..")
os.rmdir("demo_folder")
print("Folder removed!")

